# Premium UI/UX Standards

## Golden Rule: Luxury = Restraint

**Premium UIs feel expensive because they use space, typography, and color with discipline. Every pixel matters.**

---

## 1. Layout and Spacing Rules

### 1.1 8pt Grid System (MANDATORY)

**Rule**: Use an 8pt grid everywhere. No exceptions.

**Allowed spacing tokens ONLY**:
```typescript
// src/shared/constants/spacing.ts
export const SPACING = {
  0: 0,
  1: 4,   // 0.5 × 8
  2: 8,   // 1 × 8
  3: 12,  // 1.5 × 8
  4: 16,  // 2 × 8
  5: 20,  // 2.5 × 8
  6: 24,  // 3 × 8
  8: 32,  // 4 × 8
  10: 40, // 5 × 8
  12: 48, // 6 × 8
} as const;
```

**❌ FORBIDDEN**: Random spacing values (14, 18, 22, 26, 28, 30, 34, 36, 38, 42, 44, 46, etc.)

**✅ GOOD**:
```typescript
padding: SPACING[4],        // 16px
marginBottom: SPACING[6],    // 24px
gap: SPACING[2],            // 8px
```

**❌ BAD**:
```typescript
padding: 14,                // Not in 8pt grid!
marginBottom: 18,           // Not in 8pt grid!
gap: 22,                    // Not in 8pt grid!
```

**Exception**: Only if there's a **strong, documented reason** (e.g., aligning with external design system, accessibility requirement). Must be approved and documented.

---

### 1.2 Single Content Column (Disciplined Widths)

**Rule**: On phone, keep content in a centered column with consistent horizontal padding.

**Screen Padding**:
- **Compact**: `SPACING[4]` (16px) - for dense information screens
- **Premium feel**: `SPACING[5]` (20px) - default for most screens

**Card Padding**:
- **Minimum**: `SPACING[3]` (12px) - never less
- **Standard**: `SPACING[4]` (16px) - default
- **Premium**: `SPACING[5]` (20px) - for important cards

**Implementation**:
```typescript
// Screen wrapper
<View style={{
  flex: 1,
  backgroundColor: theme.background.primary,
  paddingHorizontal: SPACING[5], // 20px default
}}>
  {/* Content */}
</View>

// Card
<View style={{
  backgroundColor: theme.surface.default,
  padding: SPACING[4], // 16px default, never less than SPACING[3]
  borderRadius: BORDER_RADIUS.lg,
}}>
  {/* Card content */}
</View>
```

---

### 1.3 Vertical Rhythm (Premium Air)

**Rule**: Prefer fewer, larger gaps. Premium UIs use air.

**Spacing Guidelines**:
- **Between major sections**: `SPACING[8]` (32px) to `SPACING[10]` (40px)
- **Between related items**: `SPACING[3]` (12px) to `SPACING[4]` (16px)
- **Between label and value**: `SPACING[1]` (4px) to `SPACING[2]` (8px)

**✅ GOOD**:
```typescript
<View style={{ marginBottom: SPACING[8] }}>
  <SectionHeader />
  <SectionContent />
</View>

<View style={{ marginBottom: SPACING[3] }}>
  <Label />
  <Value />
</View>
```

**❌ BAD**:
```typescript
<View style={{ marginBottom: 10 }}> {/* Too small, not in grid */}
  <SectionHeader />
</View>
```

---

### 1.4 Alignment is Non-Negotiable

**Rule**: All text baselines align. Icons align to text centerline or baseline (pick one system-wide).

**Text Baseline Alignment**:
```typescript
// All text in a row must share the same baseline
<View style={{ flexDirection: 'row', alignItems: 'baseline' }}>
  <Text style={TEXT_STYLES.h1}>Title</Text>
  <Text style={TEXT_STYLES.caption}>Subtitle</Text>
</View>
```

**Icon Alignment**:
```typescript
// System-wide: Icons align to text centerline
<View style={{ flexDirection: 'row', alignItems: 'center' }}>
  <Icon size={20} />
  <Text style={TEXT_STYLES.body}>Label</Text>
</View>
```

**❌ FORBIDDEN**: "Visually centered but actually misaligned" layouts. Use proper flexbox alignment.

---

## 2. Typography Rules (Premium Readability)

### 2.0 Typography Pairing (From `docs/color-theme.md`)

**Rule**: To complete the "expensive" feel, use specific font pairings.

**Recommended Typography** (from `docs/color-theme.md`):
- **Headings**: Serif or high-contrast sans
  - Examples: Playfair Display, Canela, Cormorant, or Inter (tight tracking)
  - Letter spacing: Slightly increased on headings
- **Body**: Neutral, modern sans
  - Examples: Inter, Source Sans 3, IBM Plex Sans
- **Font weights**: Fewer choices (Regular, Medium, Semibold only)

**Visual Personality**:
- **Minimalist** — few colors, disciplined usage
- **Elegant** — warm gold against disciplined blues
- **Expensive** — no loud accents, no playful saturation
- **Timeless** — avoids trends, suitable for long-lived products

---

### 2.1 Limit Type Styles (Max 8)

**Rule**: Use a small, disciplined set of type styles. Maximum 8 styles.

**Recommended Premium Set**:
```typescript
// src/shared/constants/typography.ts
export const TEXT_STYLES = {
  // Display (rare, hero text)
  display: {
    fontSize: 30,           // 28-32 range
    fontWeight: FONT_WEIGHTS.semibold,
    lineHeight: 30 * 1.25,
  },
  
  // H1 (page titles)
  h1: {
    fontSize: 24,          // 22-24 range
    fontWeight: FONT_WEIGHTS.semibold,
    lineHeight: 24 * 1.25,
  },
  
  // H2 (section headers)
  h2: {
    fontSize: 20,          // 18-20 range
    fontWeight: FONT_WEIGHTS.semibold,
    lineHeight: 20 * 1.25,
  },
  
  // Body (default text)
  body: {
    fontSize: 16,         // 15-16 range
    fontWeight: FONT_WEIGHTS.regular,
    lineHeight: 16 * 1.4, // 1.35-1.5× for premium feel
  },
  
  // Body Emphasis
  bodyEmphasis: {
    fontSize: 16,         // 15-16 range
    fontWeight: FONT_WEIGHTS.medium,
    lineHeight: 16 * 1.4,
  },
  
  // Caption (helper text)
  caption: {
    fontSize: 13,         // 12-13 range
    fontWeight: FONT_WEIGHTS.regular,
    lineHeight: 13 * 1.4,
  },
  
  // Overline / Label (uppercase optional)
  overline: {
    fontSize: 12,         // 11-12 range
    fontWeight: FONT_WEIGHTS.medium,
    lineHeight: 12 * 1.4,
    textTransform: 'uppercase', // Optional, use sparingly
    letterSpacing: 0.5,
  },
} as const;
```

**❌ FORBIDDEN**: Creating new text styles without removing an old one. Max 8 total.

---

### 2.2 Body Text: Smaller Size + More Line Height

**Rule**: Prefer slightly smaller body text (15-16px) with generous line height (1.35-1.5×).

**Premium Body Text**:
```typescript
body: {
  fontSize: 16,           // Not 18px
  lineHeight: 16 * 1.4,  // 22.4px - generous spacing
  fontWeight: FONT_WEIGHTS.regular,
}
```

**Why**: This reads "considered" rather than "default." The extra line height creates breathing room.

---

### 2.3 Use Weight Sparingly (Luxury = Restraint)

**Rule**: Default is Regular. Use Medium for emphasis. Semibold for headlines only.

**Weight Hierarchy**:
- **Default**: `FONT_WEIGHTS.regular` (400)
- **Emphasis**: `FONT_WEIGHTS.medium` (500)
- **Headlines**: `FONT_WEIGHTS.semibold` (600)
- **Avoid**: `FONT_WEIGHTS.bold` (700) - too heavy for premium feel

**❌ FORBIDDEN**: Bold-heavy UIs. If everything is bold, nothing is emphasized.

---

### 2.4 Truncation Rules

**Rule**: Titles max 1-2 lines, then ellipsis. Avoid dense paragraphs.

**Implementation**:
```typescript
// Titles: 1-2 lines max
<Text
  style={TEXT_STYLES.h1}
  numberOfLines={2}
  ellipsizeMode="tail"
>
  {title}
</Text>

// Body: Break into sections, don't create walls of text
<View>
  <Text style={TEXT_STYLES.body}>{paragraph1}</Text>
  <View style={{ height: SPACING[4] }} />
  <Text style={TEXT_STYLES.body}>{paragraph2}</Text>
</View>
```

**❌ FORBIDDEN**: Dense paragraphs without breaks. Break content into digestible sections.

---

## 3. Color Rules (Keep It Expensive)

### 3.1 Neutrals Dominate; Color is a Signal

**Rule**: Neutrals = 85-95% of UI. Primary blue = 3-10%. Gold accent = 1-3%.

**Color Distribution**:
- **Neutrals** (backgrounds, text, borders): 85-95%
- **Primary blue** (links, primary actions, key highlights): 3-10%
- **Gold accent** (tiny highlights only): 1-3% (matches `docs/color-theme.md`)

**❌ FORBIDDEN**: If gold appears more than "a few touches per screen," it stops feeling premium.

**Brand Colors** (from `docs/color-theme.md`):
```typescript
// Primary Brand Color
primary: {
  main: '#0B3C78',      // Royal Blue
  hover: '#072A55',     // Midnight Blue (hover/active)
  dark: '#1E5FA8',      // Royal Blue (brighter for dark theme)
  darkHover: '#2C76C9', // Luminous Blue (dark theme hover)
},

// Luxury Accent (use sparingly - 1-3% max)
accent: {
  light: '#C9A24D',     // Antique Gold (light theme)
  dark: '#D4AF37',      // Warm Gold (dark theme)
  background: '#F3E9D2', // Champagne Tint (light theme only)
},
```

**Design Guidance** (from `docs/color-theme.md`):
- **Gold should never be dominant** — 1-3% usage max
- **Prefer thin lines, subtle shadows, and negative space**
- **Avoid gradients in light mode** — flat tones feel more premium
- **No pure black** — always navy-tinted (even in dark mode)
- **Gold works best on dark mode** — icons, focus rings, key numbers
- **Avoid glow effects** — rely on contrast and spacing instead

**Implementation**:
```typescript
// ✅ GOOD: Mostly neutrals
<View style={{ backgroundColor: theme.background.primary }}>
  <Text style={{ color: theme.text.primary }}>Neutral text</Text>
  <Button style={{ backgroundColor: theme.interactive.primary }}>Primary action</Button>
  <Icon color={theme.accent.gold} /> {/* Rare gold accent */}
</View>

// ❌ BAD: Too much color
<View style={{ backgroundColor: theme.interactive.primary }}>
  <Text style={{ color: theme.accent.gold }}>Gold text</Text>
  <Button style={{ backgroundColor: theme.accent.gold }}>Gold button</Button>
</View>
```

---

### 3.2 Never Use Pure Black or Pure White

**Rule**: Light theme uses off-white backgrounds and deep navy text. Dark theme uses near-black navy and soft ivory text.

**Light Theme** (from `docs/color-theme.md` - "Polished Luxury"):
```typescript
background: {
  primary: '#F6F7F4',    // Soft Ivory (not #FFFFFF)
  secondary: '#ECEFF1',  // Cool Platinum (cards, sections)
  elevated: '#FFFFFF',    // Elevated surfaces
},
border: {
  default: '#D1D5D8',    // Brushed Steel (dividers, borders)
},
text: {
  primary: '#0F1E2D',    // Deep Navy (not #000000)
  secondary: '#4A5D73',  // Slate Blue-Gray
  tertiary: '#8A95A3',   // Cool Gray (muted/helper text)
},
interactive: {
  primary: '#0B3C78',    // Royal Blue
  primaryHover: '#072A55', // Midnight Blue
},
accent: {
  gold: '#C9A24D',       // Antique Gold (icons, highlights)
  goldBackground: '#F3E9D2', // Champagne Tint
},
```

**Dark Theme** (from `docs/color-theme.md` - "Midnight Precision"):
```typescript
background: {
  primary: '#0A1420',    // Near-Black Navy (not #000000)
  secondary: '#121E2B',  // Deep Steel Blue (cards)
  elevated: '#182636',   // Charcoal Navy (modals)
},
border: {
  default: '#223447',    // Blue-Gray Steel (dividers, hairline accents)
},
text: {
  primary: '#E6E8E5',    // Soft Ivory (not #FFFFFF)
  secondary: '#A8B1BC',  // Muted Steel
  tertiary: '#6F7A85',   // Cool Gray (disabled/subtle)
},
interactive: {
  primary: '#1E5FA8',    // Royal Blue (brighter for contrast)
  primaryHover: '#2C76C9', // Luminous Blue
},
accent: {
  gold: '#D4AF37',       // Warm Gold (icons, focus rings, key numbers)
},
```

**Reference**: See `docs/color-theme.md` for complete color palette and design guidance.

---

### 3.3 One Accent Per Component

**Rule**: A button is either Primary (blue), Neutral (surface), or Destructive (rare, controlled). Never mix blue + gold in the same control.

**✅ GOOD**:
```typescript
// Primary button (blue)
<Button variant="primary" />

// Neutral button (surface)
<Button variant="secondary" />

// Destructive button (red, rare)
<Button variant="destructive" />
```

**❌ BAD**:
```typescript
// Mixed accents in one component
<Button style={{
  backgroundColor: theme.interactive.primary, // Blue
  borderColor: theme.accent.gold,             // Gold - NO!
}} />
```

---

## 4. Surfaces, Cards, and Borders

### 4.1 Prefer Borders Over Shadows (Especially on iOS)

**Rule**: Luxury UIs are quiet. Use hairline borders. Subtle elevation only for modals/floating elements.

**Design Guidance** (from `docs/color-theme.md`):
- **Prefer thin lines** — use `StyleSheet.hairlineWidth` or `1px` borders
- **Subtle shadows** — only for modals and floating elements
- **Negative space** — use whitespace instead of heavy visual elements
- **Avoid gradients in light mode** — flat tones feel more premium
- **Avoid glow effects** — rely on contrast and spacing instead

**Border Implementation**:
```typescript
// ✅ GOOD: Hairline border (thin line)
<View style={{
  borderWidth: StyleSheet.hairlineWidth, // or 1
  borderColor: theme.border.default,    // Brushed Steel (#D1D5D8) or Blue-Gray Steel (#223447)
  borderRadius: BORDER_RADIUS.lg,
}}>

// ✅ GOOD: Subtle shadow only for modals (not cards)
<Modal style={{
  shadowColor: '#000',
  shadowOffset: { width: 0, height: 2 },
  shadowOpacity: 0.1,  // Subtle, not heavy
  shadowRadius: 8,
  elevation: 4, // Android
}}>

// ❌ BAD: Heavy shadows everywhere
<View style={{
  shadowColor: '#000',
  shadowOffset: { width: 0, height: 10 },
  shadowOpacity: 0.3,  // Too heavy
  shadowRadius: 20,
}}>

// ❌ BAD: Gradients in light mode
<View style={{
  background: 'linear-gradient(...)', // No gradients!
}}>
```

---

### 4.2 Border Radius: Consistent and Moderate

**Rule**: Pick one radius scale and stick to it.

**Recommended Radius Scale**:
```typescript
export const BORDER_RADIUS = {
  none: 0,
  sm: 10,   // Small controls (10-12 range)
  md: 14,   // Cards (14-16 range)
  lg: 18,   // Sheets/Modals (18-24 range)
} as const;
```

**Usage**:
- **Small controls** (buttons, inputs): `BORDER_RADIUS.sm` (10-12)
- **Cards**: `BORDER_RADIUS.md` (14-16)
- **Sheets/Modals**: `BORDER_RADIUS.lg` (18-24)

**❌ FORBIDDEN**: 
- Tiny radii (looks "default")
- Excessive rounding (looks playful)
- Inconsistent radius values

---

### 4.3 Card Structure Rule

**Rule**: A card must have clear structure: header (title + optional action), content area, optional footer.

**Card Template**:
```typescript
<View style={styles.card}>
  {/* Header */}
  <View style={styles.cardHeader}>
    <Text style={TEXT_STYLES.h2}>{title}</Text>
    {action && (
      <TouchableOpacity onPress={action.onPress}>
        <Text>{action.label}</Text>
      </TouchableOpacity>
    )}
  </View>
  
  {/* Content */}
  <View style={styles.cardContent}>
    {children}
  </View>
  
  {/* Optional Footer */}
  {footer && (
    <View style={styles.cardFooter}>
      {footer}
    </View>
  )}
</View>
```

**❌ FORBIDDEN**: "Floating random content" without structure.

---

## 5. Component Rules (Buttons, Inputs, Lists)

### 5.1 Buttons

**Primary Button**:
- **Height**: `48-52px` (use `SPACING[12]` = 48px or custom 50px)
- **Radius**: `12-14px` (use `BORDER_RADIUS.sm` = 10-12, or `BORDER_RADIUS.md` = 14)
- **Text**: Medium/Semibold
- **No gradients**
- **Press state**: Darken background slightly; no ripple chaos

**Secondary Button**:
- Same size as primary
- Neutral background or border
- Never more visually dominant than primary

**Icon Buttons**:
- **Touch target min**: `44×44px` (accessibility requirement)
- **Icon size**: `18-22px`
- **One icon style set only** (stroke weight consistent)

**Implementation**:
```typescript
// Primary button
<TouchableOpacity
  style={{
    height: 50, // 48-52 range
    borderRadius: BORDER_RADIUS.md, // 14px
    backgroundColor: theme.interactive.primary,
    paddingHorizontal: SPACING[6], // 24px
    justifyContent: 'center',
    alignItems: 'center',
  }}
  activeOpacity={0.8} // Darken on press
>
  <Text style={[TEXT_STYLES.button, { color: theme.text.inverse }]}>
    {title}
  </Text>
</TouchableOpacity>

// Icon button
<TouchableOpacity
  style={{
    width: 44, // Min touch target
    height: 44,
    justifyContent: 'center',
    alignItems: 'center',
  }}
>
  <Icon size={20} color={theme.text.primary} />
</TouchableOpacity>
```

---

### 5.2 Inputs

**Input Specifications**:
- **Height**: `48-52px` (match button height)
- **Label above input** (not inside) for premium clarity
- **Border**: `1px` subtle (use `StyleSheet.hairlineWidth` or `1`)
- **Focus**: Blue focus ring or border (no neon glow)

**Implementation**:
```typescript
<View>
  <Text style={[TEXT_STYLES.label, { marginBottom: SPACING[1] }]}>
    {label}
  </Text>
  <TextInput
    style={{
      height: 50, // 48-52 range
      borderWidth: 1,
      borderColor: theme.border.default,
      borderRadius: BORDER_RADIUS.sm, // 10-12
      paddingHorizontal: SPACING[4], // 16px
      ...TEXT_STYLES.body,
    }}
    onFocus={(e) => {
      e.target.setNativeProps({ borderColor: theme.interactive.primary });
    }}
  />
</View>
```

**❌ FORBIDDEN**: Labels inside inputs (floating labels are acceptable but not preferred for premium feel).

---

### 5.3 Lists

**List Specifications**:
- **Row height**: `56-64px` (consistent)
- **Dividers**: Hairline (`StyleSheet.hairlineWidth` or `1`)
- **Layout**: Left = label; Right = value/chevron/status
- **Avoid**: "Busy" rows with 5+ elements

**Implementation**:
```typescript
<View style={{
  height: 60, // 56-64 range
  flexDirection: 'row',
  alignItems: 'center',
  justifyContent: 'space-between',
  paddingHorizontal: SPACING[4], // 16px
  borderBottomWidth: StyleSheet.hairlineWidth,
  borderBottomColor: theme.border.default,
}}>
  <Text style={TEXT_STYLES.body}>{label}</Text>
  <View style={{ flexDirection: 'row', alignItems: 'center', gap: SPACING[2] }}>
    <Text style={TEXT_STYLES.bodyEmphasis}>{value}</Text>
    <Icon name="chevron-right" size={20} />
  </View>
</View>
```

---

## 6. Motion Rules (Premium Motion, Not Flashy)

### 6.1 Micro-animations Only

**Rule**: Duration 150-220ms. Easing: standard ease-out. Use motion to clarify state changes, not decorate.

**Animation Constants**:
```typescript
// src/shared/constants/animations.ts
export const ANIMATION = {
  duration: {
    micro: 150,   // Micro-interactions
    fast: 200,    // Standard transitions
    normal: 220,  // Max for micro-animations
  },
  easing: {
    easeOut: Easing.out(Easing.ease),
  },
} as const;
```

**Usage**:
```typescript
Animated.timing(value, {
  toValue: 1,
  duration: ANIMATION.duration.fast, // 200ms
  easing: ANIMATION.easing.easeOut,
  useNativeDriver: true,
}).start();
```

---

### 6.2 Disable "Bouncy" Transitions by Default

**Rule**: Avoid spring overshoot for core navigation/controls. Springs are fine for tiny affordances (e.g., toggles) if subtle.

**✅ GOOD**:
```typescript
// Standard ease-out for navigation
Animated.timing(translateX, {
  toValue: 0,
  duration: 200,
  easing: Easing.out(Easing.ease),
}).start();
```

**❌ BAD**:
```typescript
// Bouncy spring for navigation (too playful)
Animated.spring(translateX, {
  toValue: 0,
  tension: 100,
  friction: 8,
  overshootClamping: false, // Creates bounce
}).start();
```

**Exception**: Subtle springs for toggle switches, checkboxes (tiny affordances only).

---

### 6.3 Skeleton Loading Over Spinners

**Rule**: Spinners feel cheap when overused. Use skeletons for list and card loading. Use spinners only for short actions (<1s perceived).

**✅ GOOD**:
```typescript
// Skeleton for list loading
{isLoading ? (
  <SkeletonList count={5} />
) : (
  <FlatList data={items} />
)}

// Spinner only for short actions
<Button
  loading={isSubmitting} // <1s action
  onPress={handleSubmit}
/>
```

**❌ BAD**:
```typescript
// Spinner for list loading (feels cheap)
{isLoading ? (
  <ActivityIndicator size="large" />
) : (
  <FlatList data={items} />
)}
```

---

## 7. Iconography and Imagery Rules

### 7.1 One Icon Library, One Style

**Rule**: Either all outline or all filled. Consistent stroke width.

**Implementation**:
```typescript
// Choose one icon set and stick to it
import { Icon } from '@expo/vector-icons/Ionicons';

// All icons use same style
<Icon name="home-outline" size={20} />      // Outline style
<Icon name="settings-outline" size={20} />  // Outline style
<Icon name="user-outline" size={20} />      // Outline style

// ❌ BAD: Mixed styles
<Icon name="home" size={20} />              // Filled
<Icon name="settings-outline" size={20} />  // Outline - inconsistent!
```

---

### 7.2 Photography is Rare and Intentional

**Rule**: Luxury UI uses fewer images. If images exist, use consistent aspect ratios and rounded corners.

**Guidelines**:
- Use images sparingly
- Consistent aspect ratios (e.g., 16:9, 1:1, 4:3)
- Rounded corners match card radius
- No mixed "stock photo + illustration" styles

---

## 8. Content Rules (The Hidden Luxury Lever)

### 8.1 Reduce Visible UI "Noise"

**Rule**: Fewer labels. Shorter copy. More whitespace. Fewer simultaneous call-to-actions.

**✅ GOOD**:
```typescript
// Clean, minimal
<View>
  <Text style={TEXT_STYLES.h1}>Balance</Text>
  <Text style={TEXT_STYLES.currency}>$12,345.67</Text>
</View>
```

**❌ BAD**:
```typescript
// Too much noise
<View>
  <Text style={TEXT_STYLES.label}>Current Account Balance</Text>
  <Text style={TEXT_STYLES.body}>Your balance as of today</Text>
  <Text style={TEXT_STYLES.currency}>$12,345.67</Text>
  <Text style={TEXT_STYLES.caption}>Last updated: 2 minutes ago</Text>
  <Button title="View Details" />
  <Button title="Add Transaction" />
  <Button title="Export" />
</View>
```

---

### 8.2 Numbers Should Feel "Instrument-Grade"

**Rule**: For finance/data screens, align decimals, use tabular numerals if available, keep formatting consistent.

**Implementation**:
```typescript
// Tabular numerals (monospaced numbers)
const currencyStyle = {
  ...TEXT_STYLES.currency,
  fontVariant: ['tabular-nums'], // Aligns decimals
};

// Consistent formatting
const formatCurrency = (amount: number) => {
  return new Intl.NumberFormat('en-US', {
    style: 'currency',
    currency: 'USD',
    minimumFractionDigits: 2,
    maximumFractionDigits: 2,
  }).format(amount);
};

// Aligned decimal display
<Text style={currencyStyle}>
  {formatCurrency(1234.56)}  // $1,234.56
</Text>
<Text style={currencyStyle}>
  {formatCurrency(89.12)}    // $   89.12 (aligned)
</Text>
```

---

## 9. Accessibility Rules (Luxury Must Still Be Usable)

### 9.1 Touch Targets

**Rule**: Minimum `44×44px` touch targets (iOS/Android standard).

**Implementation**:
```typescript
<TouchableOpacity
  style={{
    minWidth: 44,
    minHeight: 44,
    padding: SPACING[2], // Ensures touch target size
  }}
>
  <Icon size={20} />
</TouchableOpacity>
```

---

### 9.2 Contrast

**Rule**: Meet WCAG AA where possible (4.5:1 minimum contrast for normal text).

**Reference**: See `.cursor/rules/19-accessibility-rules.mdc` for complete accessibility guidelines.

---

### 9.3 State Communication

**Rule**: Do not communicate state by color alone. Add icon/text.

**✅ GOOD**:
```typescript
<View style={{ flexDirection: 'row', alignItems: 'center' }}>
  <Icon name="check-circle" color={theme.status.success} />
  <Text style={{ color: theme.status.success }}>Active</Text>
</View>
```

**❌ BAD**:
```typescript
// Color only (inaccessible)
<View style={{ backgroundColor: theme.status.success }} />
```

---

## 10. Practical React Native Implementation Rules

### 10.1 Design Tokens are Mandatory

**Rule**: No hard-coded hex values or spacing in components (except in the token file).

**✅ GOOD**:
```typescript
import { SPACING, BORDER_RADIUS } from '@/shared/constants/spacing';
import { theme } from '@/infrastructure/theme/theme-context';

<View style={{
  padding: SPACING[4],
  borderRadius: BORDER_RADIUS.md,
  backgroundColor: theme.background.primary,
}} />
```

**❌ BAD**:
```typescript
<View style={{
  padding: 16,              // Hard-coded!
  borderRadius: 8,         // Hard-coded!
  backgroundColor: '#FFFFFF', // Hard-coded!
}} />
```

**Token Files**:
- `src/shared/constants/spacing.ts` - All spacing values
- `src/shared/constants/typography.ts` - All typography values
- `src/shared/constants/colors.ts` - All color values (if not using theme)
- `src/infrastructure/theme/theme-context.tsx` - Theme colors

---

### 10.2 Use a Single Screen Wrapper

**Rule**: All screens should use the same scaffolding: safe area handling, background color, default padding, standard header behavior.

**Screen Wrapper Component**:
```typescript
// src/presentation/components/screen-wrapper.tsx
export const ScreenWrapper: React.FC<{
  children: React.ReactNode;
  padding?: number;
  backgroundColor?: string;
}> = ({ children, padding = SPACING[5], backgroundColor }) => {
  const { theme } = useTheme();
  const insets = useSafeAreaInsets();

  return (
    <SafeAreaView
      style={{
        flex: 1,
        backgroundColor: backgroundColor || theme.background.primary,
        paddingTop: insets.top,
        paddingBottom: insets.bottom,
      }}
    >
      <View style={{ flex: 1, paddingHorizontal: padding }}>
        {children}
      </View>
    </SafeAreaView>
  );
};

// Usage in all screens
export default function MyScreen() {
  return (
    <ScreenWrapper>
      {/* Screen content */}
    </ScreenWrapper>
  );
}
```

---

### 10.3 Enforce Component "Tiers"

**Rule**: Text → AppText (typography preset required). View → Surface/Card (surface type required). Touchable → Button (variant required).

**Component Hierarchy**:
```typescript
// Tier 1: Base components (must use tokens)
export const AppText: React.FC<{
  variant: keyof typeof TEXT_STYLES;
  children: React.ReactNode;
}> = ({ variant, children, style }) => {
  return (
    <Text style={[TEXT_STYLES[variant], style]}>
      {children}
    </Text>
  );
};

// Tier 2: Surface components
export const Surface: React.FC<{
  variant: 'default' | 'raised' | 'overlay';
  children: React.ReactNode;
}> = ({ variant, children, style }) => {
  const { theme } = useTheme();
  return (
    <View style={[
      { backgroundColor: theme.surface[variant] },
      style,
    ]}>
      {children}
    </View>
  );
};

// Tier 3: Interactive components
export const Button: React.FC<{
  variant: 'primary' | 'secondary' | 'destructive';
  title: string;
  onPress: () => void;
}> = ({ variant, title, onPress }) => {
  // Implementation with required variant
};
```

**❌ FORBIDDEN**: Creating arbitrary styles easily. If a dev can't create arbitrary styles easily, consistency improves automatically.

---

## Recommended Defaults (Strong Starting Point)

If you want a strong starting point, use these defaults:

- **Screen padding**: `SPACING[5]` (20px)
- **Card radius**: `BORDER_RADIUS.md` (14-16px)
- **Button height**: `50px` (48-52 range)
- **Border width**: `StyleSheet.hairlineWidth` or `1`
- **Body text**: `16px` with `1.4×` line height
- **Shadows**: Used only for modals and floating bars

---

## Implementation Checklist

Before marking a component/screen "complete":

- [ ] All spacing uses 8pt grid tokens (4, 8, 12, 16, 20, 24, 32, 40, 48)
- [ ] No hard-coded colors, spacing, or typography values
- [ ] Text uses one of the 8 allowed text styles
- [ ] Colors follow 85-95% neutrals, 3-10% primary, 0.5-3% accent rule
- [ ] No pure black (#000000) or pure white (#FFFFFF)
- [ ] Borders preferred over shadows (except modals)
- [ ] Consistent border radius scale
- [ ] Buttons are 48-52px height
- [ ] Inputs are 48-52px height with labels above
- [ ] List rows are 56-64px height
- [ ] Touch targets minimum 44×44px
- [ ] Animations are 150-220ms micro-animations
- [ ] No bouncy transitions (except subtle toggles)
- [ ] Skeleton loading for lists, spinners only for short actions
- [ ] One icon library, one style (all outline or all filled)
- [ ] Content is minimal (fewer labels, shorter copy, more whitespace)
- [ ] Numbers use tabular numerals and consistent formatting
- [ ] Screen uses ScreenWrapper component
- [ ] Components use enforced tiers (AppText, Surface, Button)

